cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper deals with machine learning methods and their application to data collected from external sources, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the issue of data quality and privacy, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper uses statistical learning theory, which is a subfield of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
